  text: I have all patterns and edge guidance. Here’s how the "non-dynamic array unique values from A2:A150" is done in classic Excel:

**In B2:**
```
=IFERROR(IF(MATCH(A2,$A$2:A2,0)=ROW(A2)-ROW($A$2)+1,A2,""),"")
```
- This formula in each cell checks if the current value in A2:A150 has appeared above. If not, it’s "unique-so-far" and is shown; otherwise blank. This is the legacy-friendly way to extract uniques without a dynamic array.

